#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:28 src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Average dry thermal updraft strength near mid-BL height. Subtract glider "
"descent rate to get average vario reading for cloudless thermals. Updraft "
"strengths will be stronger than this forecast if convective clouds are "
"present, since cloud condensation adds buoyancy aloft (i.e. this neglects "
"\"cloudsuck\"). W* depends upon both the surface heating and the BL depth."
msgstr ""
"Povprečna suha termalna vzponna sila blizu srednjega BL višine. Odštevanje "
"gliderska padanja za dobiček povprečne vario merilne vrednosti za nebeške "
"termale. Vzponna sila bo bistveno viša, če je prisotni konveksni oblaki, saj"
" se oblaki kondenzacije doda v zraku (torej to zanemarja \"cloudsuck\"). W* "
"odvisno od površinske toplote in BL globine."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:37
#, no-c-format
msgid "BL Wind spd"
msgstr "BL Vjetro hitrost"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The speed and direction of the vector-averaged wind in the BL. This "
"prediction can be misleading if there is a large change in wind direction "
"through the BL."
msgstr ""
"Hitrost in smer vektor-srednjega vetra v BL. To napoved lahko preoblikuje, "
"če je veliko sprememb v smeri vetra skozi BL."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "H bl"
msgstr "Višina bl"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Height of the top of the mixing layer, which for thermal convection is the "
"average top of a dry thermal. Over flat terrain, maximum thermalling heights"
" will be lower due to the glider descent rate and other factors. In the "
"presence of clouds (which release additional buoyancy aloft, creating "
"\"cloudsuck\") the updraft top will be above this forecast, but the maximum "
"thermalling height will then be limited by the cloud base. Further, when the"
" mixing results from shear turbulence rather than thermal mixing this "
"parameter is not useful for glider flying."
msgstr ""
"Višina vrha mešanice, ki za termalno konvergenco predstavlja povprečna "
"višina suhe termale. Na ravni plava je višina maksimalne termalne višine "
"nižja zaradi gliderska padanja in drugih dejavnikov. V prisotnosti oblakov "
"(ki dodajajo dodatno bujo v zraku, kar ustvari \"cloudsuck\") bo višina vrha"
" mešanice višja od napovedi, vendar maksimalna višina termalne višine "
"omejena bo z oblakom. Poleg tega, ko se mešanica nastane zaradi šira "
"turbulenca, kot je thermalna mešanica, to parameter ni uporabno za glidersko"
" vožnjo."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "dwcrit"
msgstr "kritična hitrost padca"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This parameter estimates the height above ground at which the average dry "
"updraft strength drops below 225 fpm and is expected to give better "
"quantitative numbers for the maximum cloudless thermalling height than the "
"BL Top height, especially when mixing results from vertical wind shear "
"rather than thermals. (Note: the present assumptions tend to underpredict "
"the max. thermalling height for dry conditions.) In the presence of clouds "
"the maximum thermalling height may instead be limited by the cloud base. "
"Being for \"dry\" thermals, this parameter omits the effect of "
"\"cloudsuck\"."
msgstr ""
"To parameter ocenjuje višino nad zemljom, kjer povprečna suha vzponna sila "
"pade pod 225 fpm in pričakuje da bo dobil bolj numerične podatke za "
"maksimalno nebeško termalno višino kot višina vrha mešanice BL, posebno ko "
"se mešanica nastane zaradi vertikalnega vetra šira, kot je thermalna "
"mešanica. (Pozor: trenutni napovedi podcenijo maksimalno termalno višino za "
"suhe razmere.) V prisotnosti oblakov bo maksimalna termalna višina omejena z"
" oblakom. To parameter se nanaša na \"suhe\" termale, zato izključuje vpliva"
" \"cloudsuck\"."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "bl cloud"
msgstr "zvočna oblačnost"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:53
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This parameter provides an additional means of evaluating the formation of "
"clouds within the BL and might be used either in conjunction with or instead"
" of the other cloud prediction parameters. It assumes a very simple "
"relationship between cloud cover percentage and the maximum relative "
"humidity within the BL. The cloud base height is not predicted, but is "
"expected to be below the BL Top height."
msgstr ""
"Ta parameter zagotavlja dodatno možnost ocenjevanja oblikovanja oblačnosti v"
" BL in se lahko uporablja skupaj z drugimi parametri ocenjevanja oblačnosti "
"ali pa kot nadomestni za druge parametre. Ta parameter predvideva zelo "
"enostavno odnos med povprečno deležnostjo oblačnosti in maksimalnim "
"relativnim vlaščenjem v BL. Oblikovanje višine oblaščnosti ni predvideno, "
"vendar se pričakuje, da bo pod višino vrha BL."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sfc temp"
msgstr "temperatura tal"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The temperature at a height of 2m above ground level. This can be compared "
"to observed surface temperatures as an indication of model simulation "
"accuracy; e.g. if observed surface temperatures are significantly below "
"those forecast, then soaring conditions will be poorer than forecast."
msgstr ""
"Temperatura na višini 2m nad ravni zemlje. Ta parameter lahko je porovnjan z"
" opazovanimi površinsko temperaturami kot indikator hitrosti simuliranja "
"modela; e.g., če so opazovane površinske temperature bistveno nižje od "
"napovedanih, bo se vplival na bolj slabe razmere za vzpenjanje."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "hwcrit"
msgstr "kritična hitrost vzpenjanja"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:63
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This parameter estimates the height at which the average dry updraft "
"strength drops below 225 fpm and is expected to give better quantitative "
"numbers for the maximum cloudless thermalling height than the BL Top height,"
" especially when mixing results from vertical wind shear rather than "
"thermals. (Note: the present assumptions tend to underpredict the max. "
"thermalling height for dry conditions.) In the presence of clouds the "
"maximum thermalling height may instead be limited by the cloud base. Being "
"for \"dry\" thermals, this parameter omits the effect of \"cloudsuck\"."
msgstr ""
"Ta parameter ocenjuje višino, kjer povprečna visoka vlažnost upadnega zraka "
"pade pod 225 fpm in pričakuje da bo povečal bolj numerične informacije glede"
" maksimalne neoblaščenega vzpenjanja višine kot višina BL Top, posebno ko se"
" rezultate prepoznajo iz vertikalne zgradbe zraka, ki se giblje v smeri "
"vzpenjanja. (Napomena: trenutni predvidevanja pogosto podcenijo maksimalno "
"vzpenjanje za suhe razmere.) V prisotnosti oblačnosti lahko maksimalna "
"vzpenja višina omejena bo s področjem oblaščine. Za \"suhe\" vzpenja, ta "
"parameter izključuje učinek \"cloudsuck\"."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "wblmaxmin"
msgstr "maksimalna/minimalna višina bl"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Maximum grid-area-averaged extensive upward or downward motion within the BL"
" as created by horizontal wind convergence. Positive convergence is "
"associated with local small-scale convergence lines. Negative convergence "
"(divergence) produces subsiding vertical motion, creating low-level "
"inversions which limit thermalling heights."
msgstr ""
"Najvišji povprečni grid-area-averaged intenzivno vzpon ali pad v BL, ki ga "
"ustvari horizontalni zgradba zraka. Po svetu pozitivna konvergenca je "
"povezana s lokalnimi malih skupajnih konvergenc. Negativna konvergenca "
"(divergenca) proizvede podražanje vertikalne moči, kar ustvarja nizke ravni "
"inverzij, ki omejujejo vzpenjanje višine."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "blcwbase"
msgstr "osnova blcw"

